article.headline: Lehigh 86, American 65
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Auston Rowland scored 29 and Jose Olivero added 18 to lead Lehigh to an 86-65 win over American on Friday night. American (12-12, 6-4 Patriot League) was down only 43-39 at halftime after shooting 56 percent from the floor in the first half. But Lehigh (15-8, 8-2) held American to 39 percent shooting (8-of-23) in the second half, outscoring the Eagles 43-26. Jason Thomas led American with 16 points. Andres Rodriguez and Andre Ingram each had 13. Jornavis Draughn had 10 rebounds. Both teams were hot from the 3-point line. American was 11-of-23 (48 percent), led by Thomas, who was 4-of-5. Lehigh shot even better from long range -- 13-of-19 (68 percent). Rowland was 5-of-7 on 3s; Olivero was 4-of-6.
